Rating: 4
This soup is fast, delicious, filling, and reasonably healthy, more so if you use a lean sausage as I did, like chicken andouille, and homemade vegetable stock. Would have been even better with the linguica or Spanish chorizo, I'm sure. I found mashing the potatoes unnecessary and skipped that step. I find that soups with leafy greens in them tend to taste a bit off on the second day. To fix this, I wilt the greens in a separate pan, then put them into the bowls of soup when serving, rather than into the big pot. I just wilt more greens on future days when reheating leftovers, so they are always fresh.

