Rating: 4
This soup is a hit! I have made it several times now and every time it is a success. While I like smoked chorizo, I definitely prefer fresh. From the first time I made it and every time since, I have used fresh chorizo (in a pinch I've used hot Italian and it was still great.) Bake the sausage in the oven at about 425C, turning over half way though while the soup is doing its 20 minute simmer. Slice 'em up & voila! The sausage retains more of its flavour when baked. I use about 3 sweet potatoes, 2 large and 1 smaller and the recommended amount of white potatoes. I add a bit more broth and about a tsp. of paprika. As with most soups, this one is more flavourful the day after. This will be a staple soup for years to come and it is also a great post-run meal.

